article.headline: Alabama A&M 84, Oakwood 63
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- With a career-high 18 points and 10 rebounds, Mickell Gladness helped Alabama A&M clinch an 84-63 victory over Oakwood. In seven games, Gladness, the preseason Southwestern Athletic Conference Defensive Player of the Year, has blocked 33 shots, including six Monday night. The game was close throughout the first half. Alabama A&M (4-3) pulled ahead of Oakwood with a 14-0 run, bringing the Bulldogs' to a 37-25 lead going into halftime. A&M's Trant Simpson and Kudus Ogbara both had career-high scores with 21 points and 16 points, respectively. Simpson also had five assists and four steals. Oakwood was led by James Doggette, with 12 points and nine rebounds. Alabama A&M hosts Tuskegee on Saturday.
